  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle </p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>pork mince</strong> and cook for 5-8 min or until browned all over and starting to caramelise</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-creamy-pork-leek-mushroom-stew/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, roughly tear the <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>chestnut</strong></span> <strong>mushrooms </strong></p>\n<p>Wash the<strong> leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> carefully to remove any grit from between the leaves, then top, tail and slice finely</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-creamy-pork-leek-mushroom-stew/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>pork</strong> has browned, add the <strong>chopped leek</strong> and <strong>torn mushrooms</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-6 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-creamy-pork-leek-mushroom-stew/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\n<p>Strip the <strong>thyme</strong> <strong>leaves</strong> and chop finely, discarding the stems</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-creamy-pork-leek-mushroom-stew/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the <strong>chicken stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>\n<p>Add the <strong>soft cheese</strong> to the stock – this is your <strong>creamy stock</strong></p>\n<p>Chop the <strong>potatoes</strong> into small bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-creamy-pork-leek-mushroom-stew/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>leek</strong> and <strong>mushroom</strong> have softened, add the <strong>chopped thyme</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-creamy-pork-leek-mushroom-stew/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> and <strong>creamy stock</strong></p>\n<p>Cook, covered for 15-20 min or until the potatoes are cooked through</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-creamy-pork-leek-mushroom-stew/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy pork and mushroom stew</strong> with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
